'''''Star Wars Insider'' 60''' is the sixtieth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[June 4]], [[2002]]. This issue came packaged with promotional trading cards for the [[Wizards of the Coast]] [[Attack of the Clones (TCG)|''Attack of the Clones'']] trading card game and the [[Topps]] ''Attack of the Clones'' silver foil-stamped movie card set, while the newsstand version was available in an exclusive polybag. It's also the last issue to feature the writing of longtime contributor (and former Managing Editor) [[Scott Chernoff]], who left to pursue a career in writing for television.

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm" {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader Catalog]]"
*"[[Jabba's Collection|Action Figure Update]]" &mdash; ''Attack of the Clones'' Action Figure Update
*"[[Behind the Magic]]" &mdash; Swarm Troopers {{C|by [[Rob Coleman]]}}
*"[[Gamescape]]" &mdash; Attack of the Board Games {{C|by [[Rob Daviau]]}}
*"[[Bookshelf]]" &mdash; Dark Duo {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Comics Link]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: Jango Fett: Open Seasons|''Jango Fett: Open Seasons'']] {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*"[[Set Piece]]: Theed Palace Hangar" {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]] & [[Chris Reiff]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Now That You Bought It, Where Do You Put It? {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]]" &mdash; Jar Jar Binks is 31 Today! {{C|by [[Michael Selinker]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]]" {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[The Last Page]]" {{C|by [[Drew Struzan]]}}

===Features===
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>A picture's worth a thousand words, but nobody can read a movie that vast. Here's some of what you might have missed from the first dozen times you watched [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Attack of the Clones'']].</small>
*"[[Ewan McGregor: Return of the Jedi]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>[[Ewan McGregor]] has made the role of [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] his own. The star discusses heroic dismemberments, fake mullets, and memorable lines.</small>
*"[[Natalie Portman: Forbidden Love]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>[[Queen/Legends|Queen]], [[Senator/Legends|senator]], clothes horse, temptress, and [[Battle droid/Legends|battle droid]] butt-kicker, [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|Padmé Amidala]] is a woman of many talents, and it takes a talented actress to bring her to life.</small>
*"[[Hayden Christensen: Journey to the Dark Side]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] is mad, bad, and dangerous to know. Luckily, [[Hayden Christensen]] has only two things in common with the character he portrays: he's tall and exceptionally talented.</small>
*"[[George Lucas: The Plot Thickens]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>[[George Lucas]] shares his thoughts on the history of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' saga, strange twists of fate, and a glimpse of the future.</small>
*"[[Exclusive Fiction|''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[R. A. Salvatore]]}}
*:<small>Take a peek at the [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones (novelization)|novelization]], and feast your eyes on some fantastic images from the film.</small>
*"[[The Droids of Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Sneaky, faithful, or just plain deadly, the droids of ''Attack of the Clones'' come in all shapes and sizes.</small>
*"[[Who's Who in Jabba's Palace]]" {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*:<small>That [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|cantina]] was a children's theme park compared to this den of scum and villainy.</small>
*"[[Back on Topps: Return of the Trading Cards]]" {{C|by [[Chris Fawcett]]}}
*:<small>We take a look at what's in the cards for recent and upcoming ''Star Wars'' collecting.</small>
*"[[Anthony Heald: Man of 1,000 Voices]]" {{C|by [[Rich Handley]]}}
*:<small>Maybe you recognize him as Dr. Frederick Childon or Vice Principal Scott Guber, but [[Anthony Heald]] has more ''Star Wars'' acting credits than anyone who appeared in the movies.</small>

